Fellow epic bards, lend me your ear.<br>
<br>
Last night I rallied a few men and woman from my guild to go out and hunt down Eldrig the Old.  When arriving in the Skyfire zone we swiftly made our way to /loc pos 500 neg 4000.  With our backs hugged up against the zone wall, facing westward we commenced to kill everything on the PH list.<br>
<br>
Bottomless feasters<br>
Skyash/skycinder drakes<br>
Wurms<br>
Mature wurms<br>
Wyverns<br>
Chromodracs<br>
<br>
Following the nicely done write up on EQ Diva to the “T” we were unable to get Eldrig to spawn.<br>
<br>
Have any of you seen this mob spawn at any other location then the loc given above?<br>
<br>
Were we doing the wrong thing by just sitting at the loc and having one person go out and attempt to kill the PH?<br>
<br>
I fear that maybe we should of killed evey pop that spawned right in front of us (facing due West) about 500 yards away from the reported loc of pos 500 neg 4000.<br>
<br>
Looking for tips, advice and or personal loc sightings to compile and assist me in my next journey to Skyfire.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
